-- `Don't Ask, Don't Tell' Injunction Won't Be Lifted While Military Appeals
-- B y   E d v a r d   P e t t e r s s o n
-- 2010-10-20T00:42:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-20/-don-t-ask-don-t-tell-injunction-won-t-be-lifted-while-military-appeals.html
A federal judge denied a government
request to stay her injunction against the “Don’t Ask, Don’t
Tell” law prohibiting gay and lesbians from serving openly in
the military while the government appeals her ruling that the
law is unconstitutional.  To contact the reporter on this story:
